---
title: Turkey Ragù Gnocchi with Peas & Italian Cheese
description: New to gnocchi? Welcome to a whole new world of comforting, carby-goodness. This Italian classic combines flour and potatoes to create darling little dumplings perfect for submerging in every kind of sauce. Here, gnocchi gets tossed with creamy turkey ragù and green peas for pops of sweetness and color. A blanket of Italian cheese tucks everything in, then a quick nap in the oven turns the ragù hot and bubbly. Serve it up family style—then sit back, relax, and enjoy some mesmerizing cheese-pulls.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/turkey-ragu-gnocchi-e00b92a8.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/turkey-ragu-gnocchi-614b4a15e6359943a26f0364-b34fe6dc.pdf
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 740 kcal
  fat: 34 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 68 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 45 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1670 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/turkey-ragu-gnocchi-614b4a15e6359943a26f0364
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
---

Heat broiler to high. Bring a #medium pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil (use a
#large pot{} for 4 servings). Wash and dry produce.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large ovenproof pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%oz}, half the @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}
(all for 4), and @salt{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4). Cook, breaking up meat into
pieces, until browned, ~{3-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking later).

Once water is boiling, add @gnocchi{8.8%oz} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until tender and floating to the top, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Add @tomato paste{1.5%oz} to pan with turkey; cook, stirring, until combined,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @cream cheese{4%tbsp}, and ½ cup pasta
cooking water (¾ cup for 4 servings) until combined.

Add @peas{4%oz}; simmer, stirring occasionally, until sauce has slightly thickened
and turkey is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Add drained gnocchi to pan with sauce; cook until warmed through,
~{1-2%minutes}. (TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water
a splash at a time until gnocchi is thoroughly coated in sauce.) Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{} to taste. TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof,
transfer mixture now to a #baking dish{}.

Evenly sprinkle with @Italian cheese blend{1/2%cup}. Broil until cheese is
melted and bubbly, ~{2-3%minutes}. TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Serve directly from pan.

> New to gnocchi? Welcome to a whole new world of comforting, carby-goodness.
> This Italian classic combines flour and potatoes to create darling little
> dumplings perfect for submerging in every kind of sauce. Here, gnocchi gets
> tossed with creamy turkey ragù and green peas for pops of sweetness and color.
> A blanket of Italian cheese tucks everything in, then a quick nap in the
> oven turns the ragù hot and bubbly. Serve it up family style—then sit back,
> relax, and enjoy some mesmerizing cheese-pulls.